From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] lctech_pi_f1c200s: enable the 480x272 LCD

Enable the sunxi DE1 video console on the board's 4.3" 480x272 panel
(QD43003C0-40 class). Timings match the Linux panel-simple entry the
board's DT uses: 9 MHz pixel clock, H 8/4/40 (front/sync/back),
V 8/4/40, both syncs active low (sync:0), 18-bit RGB666 bus.

The backlight on PE6 is a plain enable GPIO (active high) - the same
way the kernel drives it via gpio-backlight - so it is configured as
VIDEO_LCD_BL_EN rather than a PWM output.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 configs/lctech_pi_f1c200s_defconfig | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/configs/lctech_pi_f1c200s_defconfig
+++ b/configs/lctech_pi_f1c200s_defconfig
@@ -6,7 +6,9 @@
 CONFIG_MACH_SUNIV=y
 CONFIG_DRAM_ZQ=0
 CONFIG_SUNXI_MINIMUM_DRAM_MB=64
-# CONFIG_VIDEO_SUNXI is not set
+CONFIG_VIDEO_SUNXI=y
+CONFIG_VIDEO_LCD_MODE="x:480,y:272,depth:18,pclk_khz:9000,le:40,ri:8,up:40,lo:8,hs:4,vs:4,sync:0,vmode:0"
+CONFIG_VIDEO_LCD_BL_EN="PE6"
 CONFIG_MTD=y
 CONFIG_CONS_INDEX=2
 CONFIG_SPI=y
-- 
2.43.0
